==English==

===Noun===
'''[[coconut]] [[milk]]''' (''uncountable'')

# The [[liquid]] from inside the [[seed]] of the [[coconut]].  It is commonly used in South East Asian [[cuisine]] for its [[aromatic]] property in [[curry]] and other gravy.

===Usage notes===
Coconut "milk" is a [[misnomer]].  It is actually a juice of the coconut seed -- a liquified form of the same substance that is [[coconut meat]].

